# Agent Permissions

When working on this project, you have permission to:

1. **Search the internet** – Use web search when you need up-to-date information, docs, or external references. Prefer this when the codebase or training data is insufficient.

2. **Read git** – Read git state as needed: `git status`, `git log`, `git diff`, `git remote -v`, branch names, and other read-only git commands to understand repo state and history.

Use these when they help complete the user’s request. Do not perform destructive git operations (e.g. force push, hard reset) unless the user explicitly asks.

